    "what_description": "Pentameris dentata is a species of grass in the family Poaceae. It is an annual or perennial herb with culms up to 30 cm tall and 1-2 mm in diameter, having a single node. The leaves are 10-20 cm long, 0.5-1.5 mm wide, and have a keel with a prominent midrib. The spikelets are 3-4 mm long, consisting of 3-4 florets, with the lower floret sterile and the upper ones fertile. The species is native to South Africa and has a distribution range limited to the Western Cape and Eastern Cape provinces.",
